 Service Law-Civil Servant-confidential reports-Adverse remarks-Representation against adverse remarks-Rajection of representation-Held rejection of representation neither adversely affects any vested right of Government servant nor does visit him with any civil consequences-In the absence of any statutory rule or provision the competent authority is under no obligation to record or communicate reasons for its decision to Government servant.
